libmemcached (C and C++ library for memcached)
libmemcached is a C and C++ client library to the memcached
server (also available on builds.slamd64.com).

It is designed to be light on memory usage, thread-safe, and
clomplete.

It supports both synchronous and asynchronus access, TCP and
UNIX sockets, and several different hash algorithms.

Several command line utilities are also included:
  memcat - copy the value of a key to standard output
  memflush - flush the contents of the servers
  memrm - remove a key from the server
  memcp - copy fiels to a memcached server
  memstat - dump statistics of a server
  memslap - generate testing loads on a memcached cluster
